	<title>General</title>
	<p id="_aa760905-ae52-4654-9712-dd6826a867bf">The Confium framework provides a mechanism of identifying and facilitating reuse of cryptographic schemes. By allowing potential multiplexing and adoption of multiple cryptographic libraries, authors of cryptographic scheme modules can be free from fear of an updated underlying cryptographic library accidentally breaking compatibility.</p>
	</clause>
	<clause id="_reuse_of_cryptographic_components" obligation="normative">
